#!/bin/sh
#
# Configured as part of the DigitalOcean 1-Click Image build process

myip=$(hostname -I | awk '{print$1}')
cat <<EOF
********************************************************************************

Welcome to Plex Media Server

Stream your personal media library to nearly any device.

Access Plex:

  Web (via NGINX):  http://$myip
  Direct:           http://$myip:32400/web

IMPORTANT — First-time claim (unclaimed servers):

  Plex only allows initial claiming from localhost. Opening the public
  IP in a browser often shows "Not authorised". Use one of these:

  Option A — SSH tunnel (from your laptop):
    ssh -L 8888:127.0.0.1:32400 root@$myip
    Then open: http://localhost:8888/web

  Option B — Claim token:
    1. Open https://www.plex.tv/claim and copy the token
    2. Run: /opt/claim-plex.sh claim-XXXXXXXX

Media directory:

  /opt/plex/media  (in Plex UI this is /data)

Management:

  Start:    /opt/start-plex.sh
  Stop:     /opt/stop-plex.sh
  Restart:  /opt/restart-plex.sh
  Update:   /opt/update-plex.sh
  Claim:    /opt/claim-plex.sh <token>
  Logs:     docker compose -f /opt/plex/docker-compose.yml logs -f
  Status:   systemctl status plex

After claiming, configure Remote Access on port 32400 in Plex settings.

Documentation: https://www.akamai.com/cloud/marketplace-docs/guides/plex/

********************************************************************************
To delete this message of the day: rm -rf \$(readlink -f \${0})
EOF
